<h2>LATEST SUMMARIES</h2>
<p xmlns=""></p>
<b><font style="text-transform: uppercase;">Education Law, Juvenile 
Law</font></b>
<br>
<b><a name="C064967"></a><a href="http://login.findlaw.com/scripts/callaw?dest=ca/caapp4th/slip/2012/c064967.html&DCMP=NWL-pro_calapp">In re 
Q.N., No. C064967</a></b>
<br>A juvenile court's order requiring the County Office of Education to 
initiate and fund the educational placement of a minor is reversed and remanded 
where, in light of the fact that the court denied the minor's motion to join the 
Office of Education as a party, it lacked jurisdiction in ordering the Officer of
 Education to fund the minor's residential facility 
placement.&nbsp;<a href="http://login.findlaw.com/scripts/callaw?dest=ca/caapp4th/slip/2012/c064967.html&DCMP=NWL-pro_calapp">Read more...</a>
<br><br>
Related Resources<br>
&bull; <a href="http://technology.findlaw.com/mobile/defense-attorneys-letting-suspects-use-cell-phones-not-a-good-id.html">Defense Attorneys Letting Suspects Use Cell Phones, Not a Good Idea</a><br>
&bull; <a href="http://technology.findlaw.com/legal-software/">Criminal Case Management Software</a><br>
<br><br>
<p></p>
<b><font style="text-transform: uppercase;">Administrative Law, Civil Procedure, Labor & Employment 
Law</font></b>
<br>
<b><a name="D058353"></a><a href="http://login.findlaw.com/scripts/callaw?dest=ca/caapp4th/slip/2012/d058353.html&DCMP=NWL-pro_calapp">Basurto v. Imperial Irrigation 
Dist., No. D058353</a></b>
<br>In plaintiff's suit for age and/or race discrimination and wrongful 
termination against his former employer, Imperial Irrigation District (District), 
trial court's grant of defendant's motion for summary judgment is affirmed 
where: 1) the District's internal grievance procedures are sufficiently 
"judicial" in character for collateral estoppel to bar plaintiff's civil damages 
claims; 2) the threshold requirements for application of collateral estoppel are 
met in this case; and 3) plaintiff's claim that the District Board could never
 be impartial as a decision maker when a ruling in an employee's favor could
 have an adverse financial consequence for the District is without 
merit.&nbsp;<a href="http://login.findlaw.com/scripts/callaw?dest=ca/caapp4th/slip/2012/d058353.html&DCMP=NWL-pro_calapp">Read more...</a>
<br><br>
Related Resources<br>
&bull; <a href="http://corporate.findlaw.com/human-resources/nlrb-issues-advice-memos-on-employment-at-will-policies.html">NLRB Issues Advice Memos on Employment At-Will Policies</a><br>
&bull; <a href="http://corporate.findlaw.com">More Articles on HR Laws</a><br>
